This paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category as it focuses on robotic automation in surgery. Additionally, the use of deep learning for feature extraction suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The integration of deep neural networks also suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the use of publicly available datasets and analysis of tracking performance suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
